verses.roman:
ei ta' prastāve āche bahuta vicāra
grantha-bāhulya-bhaye nāri likhibāra

synonyms: ei ta'-in this; prastāve—statement; āche—there are; bahuta—many; vicāra—considerations; grantha—of the book; bāhulya—of the expansion; bhaye—out of fear; nāri—I do not; likhibāra—write.
translation: In this statement there are many confidential considerations. I do not write of them all, fearing an unnecessary increase in the volume of the book.
